# Services

## Structure
Services contain reusable business logic, separated from Vue components.

```
src/services/
├── analysis/           # Analysis algorithms
│   ├── index.ts        # Qualitative analysis (soundness, structure)
│   └── metricsCalculator.ts  # Process metrics
├── file/               # File operations
│   ├── fileService.ts  # Import/export coordination
│   ├── pnmlParser.ts   # Read PNML
│   ├── pnmlWriter.ts   # Write PNML
│   ├── jsonParser.ts   # JSON import/export
│   └── imageExporter.ts # SVG/PNG export
├── simulation/         # Simulation
│   ├── SimulationEngine.ts  # Discrete event simulation
│   └── XESExporter.ts       # XES log export
└── templates/          # Templates
    └── petriNetTemplates.ts  # Example nets
```

## Service Patterns
```typescript
// Singleton export for simple services
export const fileService = {
  async importFile(file: File): Promise<ImportResult> { /* ... */ },
  async exportToFile(net: PetriNet, options: ExportOptions): Promise<void> { /* ... */ },
}

// Class for complex services with state
export class SimulationEngine {
  constructor(net: PetriNet, config: SimulationConfig) { /* ... */ }
  run(): SimulationResult { /* ... */ }
}
```

## File Service
```typescript
// Import
const result = await fileService.importFile(file)
if (result.success) {
  store.loadNet(result.net)
}

// Export
await fileService.exportToFile(net, {
  format: 'pnml',  // or 'json'
  includeLayout: true,
  filename: 'mynet.pnml'
})
```

## Simulation Engine
```typescript
const engine = new SimulationEngine(net, {
  cases: 100,
  maxTime: 3600,
  timeModel: { type: 'exponential', mean: 10 }
})
const result = engine.run()
// result.statistics, result.eventLog, etc.
```

## Templates
```typescript
import { templates, getTemplatesByCategory } from '@/services/templates/petriNetTemplates'

// All templates
templates.forEach(t => console.log(t.nameKey))

// By category
const basicTemplates = getTemplatesByCategory('basic')

// Load template
const net = template.create()
store.loadNet(net)
```

## Error Handling
- Services throw exceptions on errors
- Components catch these and show user feedback
- Return import errors as `ImportResult.errors[]`
